
=== Build Gear Installation ===

1. Requirements

   To compile Build Gear the following dependencies must be installed on your
   build system:

    * g++ (C++11 enabled)
    * libcurl4-gnutls-dev
    * termcap

   Note: termcap is usually bundled with ncurses/curses.


2. Install steps (general)

   ./configure
   make
   make install

   See ./configure --help for more options.


3. Install steps (Ubuntu)

   Tested using Ubuntu 12.10 64-bit (Minimal)

   Prepare Ubuntu for compilation and installation of Build Gear
   $ sudo apt-get install build-essential libcurl4-gnutls-dev libncurses5-dev unzip

   Build and install Build Gear:
   $ wget http://www.buildgear.org/release/buildgear-0.9.15beta.tar.xz
   $ tar xf buildgear-0.9.15beta.tar.xz
   $ cd buildgear-0.9.15beta
   $ ./configure --prefix=$HOME/opt/buildgear
   $ make
   $ make install

   Add Build Gear to your path, eg.:
   $ echo 'export PATH=$HOME/opt/buildgear/bin:$PATH' >> ~/.bashrc

   Enable Build Gear bash auto completion, eg.:
   $ echo 'source $HOME/opt/buildgear/etc/bash_completion.d/buildgear-bash-completion.sh' >> ~/.bashrc

